31/10/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Economy Minister Stevco Jakimovski met with Kosovo's Trade and Industry Minister Ali Jakupi in Skopje on Friday (29 October). Afterwards, the two indicated they are working to boost economic and trade co-operation. Measures might include the signing of a Free Trade Agreement, separate from the one sealed between Macedonia and Serbia-Montenegro. According to Jakimovski, the proposal came from Kosovo. He added that Skopje has the political will for talks with Kosovo institutions directly. (Vest, A1 TV, KosovaLive - 30/10/04)
